HEADWORD: Ceramics
<hw>Ce*ram"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Ceramic</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of making things of
baked clay; as pottery, tiles, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Work formed of clay in whole or in
part, and baked; <as>as, vases, urns, etc.</as></def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerargyrite</ent>⟦br⟧
